Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as Magnetic Resonance Fingerprint (MRF) is a technique used in medical imaging and is related to image processing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses fast approximate nearest neighbour searches and iterative reconstruction algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possibility as the paper discusses dictionary learning and matching. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of cover trees for efficient searching. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also relevant as the paper discusses the computational aspects of MRF reconstruction.
